latest_video_title: sisibo podcast episode 28
description:
Conferred City status on the 15th day of August 2024, Eldoret is located in western Kenya, south of Cherangany Hills.  The town came into being in the year 1910 with the construction of a post office on a site, which was known to the white settlers as Farm 64, 64 or Sisibo. The locals at that time referred to the town as Farm 64 or Sisibo because, the town of Eldoret was 64 miles away from the newly established Uganda Railway railhead, located at Kibigori.

Bethel Studios KE prides in documenting and sharing the rich life and history of Eldoret ranging from politics, healthcare, education, art, business, farming, athletics and many more aspects of the great Eldoret City. 

Please write to us on bethelstudioske@gmail.com or call 0723433576 for a feature in this podcast.
